Key Match Events: Weston Wilson drove in the tiebreaking run with an infield single down the third-base line.
Nick Castellanos homered to left center (370 feet), Turner scored.
Jonathan Aranda homered to right (391 feet).
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Philadelphia Phillies completed a three-game sweep against the Tampa Bay Rays.
The game was held at Citizens Bank Park with an attendance of 40,715.
Zack Wheeler pitched 6.0 innings with 4 hits, 2 earned runs, 9 strikeouts, and 3 walks.
Carlos Estevez earned his 25th save of the season.
